properties.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued February 7 at 7:45PM EST until February 7 at 10:00PM EST by NWS Baltimore MD/Washington DC
properties.description:
* WHAT...Up to one foot of inundation above ground level in low
lying areas due to tidal flooding.

* WHERE...Shoreline in Southeast Harford County.

* WHEN...Until 10 PM EST this evening, especially around the
time of high tide.

* IMPACTS...At 4.0 feet, water begins to go over the bulkhead at
the Havre de Grace Yacht Basin in multiple locations.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Tides two to two and a half feet above
normal. The next high tide at Havre de Grace is at 8:12 PM.
properties.instruction:
If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be
closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of
unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone
property.

NWSheadline: COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 PM EST THIS EVENING
